item.description:
At CopenhagenJS in August I was able to share my work on Renovate—a universal dependency update tool—and how you can use it to save time and improve security in software projects.
If you want to find out more about Renovate you can find us on GitHub.
.embed-container { position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; max-width: 100%; } .embed-container iframe, .embed-container object, .embed-container embed { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; }

I&rsquo;m a recent graduate from the University of Cambridge, with an MEng in instrumentation and control engineering. During my time at Cambridge I rowed for my college boat club, represented the university in athletics, and occasionally moonlighted as a balloon artist.
Since graduating I&rsquo;ve moved to Copenhagen, Denmark and am enjoying every second of it (except the weather). I&rsquo;m currently working for Microsoft as a software developer.
This site is my online home for all things code, or otherwise&hellip;
